1
00:00:39,520 --> 00:00:40,320
Thank you.

2
00:00:42,159 --> 00:00:42,960
For what?

3
00:00:44,159 --> 00:00:45,520
Thanks for always being by my side.

4
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:47,119
I don't really have a way to repay you.

5
00:00:50,039 --> 00:00:50,880
Repay?

6
00:00:51,240 --> 00:00:53,320
Well, there is a way, if you want.

7
00:00:54,359 --> 00:00:55,119
What is it?

8
00:00:58,079 --> 00:00:58,920
Go back abroad with me.

9
00:01:08,359 --> 00:01:09,359
Right now,

10
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:10,640
we don't even have a clue

11
00:01:10,640 --> 00:01:12,079
where the next Lingxiao Pearl is.

12
00:01:12,840 --> 00:01:15,079
You can't just keep wasting time like this.

13
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:18,599
What if I told you I have a lead?

14
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:33,640
Beautiful dreams,

15
00:01:34,359 --> 00:01:35,879
like beautiful poems,

16
00:01:36,439 --> 00:01:38,319
can't be forced, only encountered.

17
00:01:39,719 --> 00:01:43,120
They appear when you least expect them.

18
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:47,239
And I think beautiful people are even more so.

19
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:57,040
Bai Lingling once mentioned

20
00:01:57,159 --> 00:01:57,959
that the head of their organization

21
00:01:57,959 --> 00:01:59,760
holds many leads on the Lingxiao Pearls.

22
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:01,599
He's been secretly investigating too.

23
00:02:01,799 --> 00:02:02,680
So I believe

24
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:03,519
this Ghost Eye

25
00:02:03,519 --> 00:02:05,159
is very likely the Lingxiao Pearl.

26
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:10,280
Jumping to conclusions from a few words

27
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:11,159
seems a bit hasty, don't you think?

28
00:02:11,159 --> 00:02:12,080
It's fine.

29
00:02:12,159 --> 00:02:13,599
I'll go see Curator Zhu when I get back

30
00:02:13,599 --> 00:02:15,199
and see if he has any new findings.

31
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:18,599
I just feel that

32
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:21,520
the Kunlun Mountains are too treacherous.

33
00:02:22,120 --> 00:02:24,800
I'm worried, given your health.

34
00:02:27,599 --> 00:02:28,639
But it's okay.

35
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:30,479
I won't give up.

36
00:02:30,879 --> 00:02:32,120
Having a lead is a good thing.

37
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,479
I'll go searching with you.

38
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:40,199
So, what do you do?

39
00:02:42,599 --> 00:02:45,560
I'm an archaeologist.

40
00:02:46,639 --> 00:02:47,800
In my spare time,

41
00:02:48,159 --> 00:02:50,599
I help restore antiques for the state.

42
00:02:51,199 --> 00:02:53,599
Things like ancient swords, ancient zithers,

43
00:02:54,159 --> 00:02:55,120
that sort of stuff.

44
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:56,719
Nothing worth mentioning.

45
00:02:56,719 --> 00:02:58,759
Wow, you're really impressive!

46
00:02:59,479 --> 00:03:00,719
Oh, hardly impressive.

47
00:03:01,439 --> 00:03:02,439
But impressive?

48
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:03,479
Yeah, that I am.

49
00:03:04,159 --> 00:03:05,879
Just ask around in archaeology circles.

50
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:07,919
The name Lu Di, well, definitely...

51
00:03:13,639 --> 00:03:14,439
How rude.

52
00:03:14,439 --> 00:03:16,360
So what brings you here?

53
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:17,719
Don't even ask.

54
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:19,680
There's a big tomb out here.

55
00:03:20,159 --> 00:03:20,919
A big tomb?

56
00:03:20,919 --> 00:03:21,680
Big herd.

57
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:23,719
We're going over to discuss

58
00:03:23,719 --> 00:03:25,599
raising cattle, sheep, you know,

59
00:03:25,599 --> 00:03:27,400
livestock-related projects.

60
00:03:28,479 --> 00:03:29,319
Yes, yes, exactly.

61
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:37,840
Cheers.

62
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:40,919
Come on, sit, sit.

63
00:03:41,879 --> 00:03:43,080
What kind of liquor is this? So strong.

64
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:45,400
Erguotou.

65
00:03:47,319 --> 00:03:49,080
Let's be clear, it's my treat today.

66
00:03:49,719 --> 00:03:50,560
Why is that?

67
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:51,479
This trip,

68
00:03:51,479 --> 00:03:53,039
I caused everyone a lot of trouble.

69
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,520
Well, aren't you polite.

70
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:56,199
When have you ever not caused trouble?

71
00:03:56,199 --> 00:03:56,919
Right, right, right.

72
00:03:57,439 --> 00:03:58,599
Then I won't hold back.

73
00:03:58,599 --> 00:03:59,400
Don't.

74
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:00,280
Waiter!

75
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:02,599
Two more plates of fresh lamb.

76
00:04:03,599 --> 00:04:04,319
Old Chen.

77
00:04:04,439 --> 00:04:05,680
You and I have to drink to this.

78
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:06,719
Come on.

79
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:11,599
Your place got blown up like that,

80
00:04:11,599 --> 00:04:12,960
you can't live there anymore, right?

81
00:04:13,879 --> 00:04:15,400
I've got an idea for you, buddy.

82
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:16,600
Just go with the flow.

83
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:19,839
Tonight, you go with Advisor He

84
00:04:19,839 --> 00:04:20,839
back to her hotel.

85
00:04:20,839 --> 00:04:21,720
Get lost.

86
00:04:22,879 --> 00:04:23,959
I'm going home with you tonight.

87
00:04:24,399 --> 00:04:25,480
Don't count on me.

88
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:26,759
I've got a date tonight.

89
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:28,959
You've got a date?

90
00:04:29,319 --> 00:04:31,000
This girl, a real babe.

91
00:04:31,399 --> 00:04:32,480
Real tall.

92
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:34,079
Gorgeous.

93
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:37,600
Lao Lu.

94
00:04:38,079 --> 00:04:39,560
I'll crash at your place.

95
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:40,399
Sure, sure.

96
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:41,279
Dad?

97
00:04:42,519 --> 00:04:43,199
Dad.

98
00:04:43,199 --> 00:04:45,439
My, my dad...

99
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:47,040
He's sick.

100
00:04:47,199 --> 00:04:48,480
Yeah, not feeling well.

101
00:04:48,519 --> 00:04:50,199
He said he'd stay with me for a couple of days.

102
00:04:50,199 --> 00:04:51,720
Look at this... talk about bad timing, huh?

103
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:52,680
I know about that.

104
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:54,160
Find somewhere else.

105
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:55,360
I'm telling you, Old Chen,

106
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:56,680
this is fate.

107
00:04:57,160 --> 00:04:58,160
Destined by heaven.

108
00:04:58,399 --> 00:04:59,240
There are three of us.

109
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,639
Forget about us two.

110
00:05:00,639 --> 00:05:02,399
You can only beg Advisor He

111
00:05:02,439 --> 00:05:03,439
to take you in.

112
00:05:03,639 --> 00:05:05,199
Advisor He, do me a favor.

113
00:05:05,199 --> 00:05:06,480
This kid's pretty pitiful.

114
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:08,000
Why don't you take him in?

115
00:05:08,079 --> 00:05:08,839
No problem.

116
00:05:08,959 --> 00:05:10,079
My hotel room is a suite.

117
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,279
I'll leave a bed for you.

118
00:05:11,279 --> 00:05:12,480
No, no, no.

119
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:14,839
Are you kidding me?

120
00:05:15,639 --> 00:05:17,199
I'll just leave my luggage with you...

121
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:18,360
I just remembered something.

122
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:20,680
I need to hit the bathhouse for a scrub first.

123
00:05:20,759 --> 00:05:22,360
Wash off this dusty stench.

124
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:23,959
Then I've got to go pick up that girl.

125
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:25,879
You two chat, I'm off, Advisor He.

126
00:05:25,959 --> 00:05:27,160
Thanks for taking him in.

127
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:28,800
Don't you pay the bill.

128
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:29,519
I'll pay, I'll pay.

129
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:30,560
I'll, I'll get it.

130
00:05:32,199 --> 00:05:32,680
Oh, right.

131
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:33,720
I have something to tell you.

132
00:05:34,639 --> 00:05:35,480
What is it?

133
00:05:36,439 --> 00:05:38,560
The info on Ding Dawei's dagger

134
00:05:39,079 --> 00:05:41,279
is vague, and the scope is too broad.

135
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:43,319
And it's in the Kunlun Mountains.

136
00:05:43,839 --> 00:05:45,480
I don't want you taking that risk.

137
00:05:46,279 --> 00:05:46,920
Right.

138
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:48,920
You're absolutely right.

139
00:05:50,639 --> 00:05:51,759
I'm absolutely right.

140
00:05:51,879 --> 00:05:53,600
But you just won't listen, will you?

141
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:54,759
I didn't say that.

142
00:05:55,439 --> 00:05:56,399
So you'll listen?

143
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:00,680
Fine.

144
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,319
No problem.

145
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:07,040
Good boy.

146
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:15,680
Sir, we're here.

147
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,160
Why'd you drive here?

148
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:18,920
Isn't this your home?

149
00:06:20,319 --> 00:06:21,439
You're telling me to go home?

150
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:23,319
Where else would you want to go?

151
00:06:36,399 --> 00:06:37,160
Little Chen.

152
00:06:44,519 --> 00:06:45,199
Old Zhu.

153
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,399
Did Advisor He ask you

154
00:06:47,399 --> 00:06:48,680
to help clean this up?

155
00:06:48,879 --> 00:06:49,720
Something like this,

156
00:06:49,839 --> 00:06:52,160
only Miss He would think to do for you.

157
00:06:52,879 --> 00:06:53,680
Kid,

158
00:06:53,959 --> 00:06:56,319
you owe her more and more favors.

159
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:02,600
A few days after I got back from Jinghong,

160
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:06,240
I received a document from the Northwest.

161
00:07:06,519 --> 00:07:07,560
The sender

162
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:09,639
was an old college classmate of mine,

163
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,920
now a professor at the Institute of Geology.

164
00:07:12,759 --> 00:07:14,199
The letter basically said

165
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:17,040
that while doing geological surveys in the Northwest,

166
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:19,279
near Xiaduo Yuzhang Mountain,

167
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:20,600
they found a huge pit.

168
00:07:22,759 --> 00:07:24,920
An eye pattern made of animal bones?

169
00:07:26,199 --> 00:07:27,319
I believe so.

170
00:07:28,199 --> 00:07:29,279
How was it formed?

171
00:07:31,199 --> 00:07:32,279
He wasn't sure.

172
00:07:32,959 --> 00:07:33,720
He just said

173
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:36,720
there were no signs of habitation in the area,

174
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:38,920
nor any traces of human life.

175
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:40,319
Hold on.

176
00:07:53,399 --> 00:07:55,040
I mentioned to you on the phone before

177
00:07:55,079 --> 00:07:57,040
that Ding Dawei, who went into the tomb with us,

178
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:59,040
and Bai Lingling were hired by the same person.

179
00:07:59,519 --> 00:08:00,600
I've talked to him too.

180
00:08:00,759 --> 00:08:01,720
I suspect

181
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:04,480
this is the clue to the next Lingxiao Pearl.

182
00:08:05,319 --> 00:08:06,600
Combined with this photo of yours,

183
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,600
I'm even more sure my guess is right.

184
00:08:09,199 --> 00:08:09,959
What are you going to do?

185
00:08:10,639 --> 00:08:11,279
Go explore it.

186
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:12,920
Maybe.

187
00:08:14,439 --> 00:08:15,680
What's going on?

188
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:17,360
You'd never hesitate before

189
00:08:17,639 --> 00:08:19,000
when I told you about things like this.

190
00:08:20,399 --> 00:08:21,680
That place is so mysterious.

191
00:08:21,839 --> 00:08:23,399
How can we go without any preparation?

192
00:08:23,639 --> 00:08:25,120
I need to check the relevant materials first.

193
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:26,720
Fair enough.

194
00:08:27,439 --> 00:08:28,160
Tell you what,

195
00:08:28,399 --> 00:08:30,120
let me know whatever you need.

196
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:35,200
Coming!

197
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:37,960
This door of mine

198
00:08:38,159 --> 00:08:39,320
is going to get smashed by you sooner or later.

199
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:40,960
The sun's already high in the sky.

200
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:41,879
You're still not up?

201
00:08:41,879 --> 00:08:43,080
I was reading all night last night.

202
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:44,000
Didn't sleep till dawn.

203
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,039
Reading?

204
00:08:45,399 --> 00:08:47,039
What book got you so interested?

205
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,720
We're heading into their territory, right?

206
00:08:49,840 --> 00:08:51,919
Know yourself and your enemy, win every battle.

207
00:08:53,679 --> 00:08:54,559
My goodness.

208
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,399
I never knew you were such a diligent person.

209
00:08:58,320 --> 00:08:59,279
What's that supposed to mean?

210
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:01,440
It means you're doing well.

211
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:05,360
You reap what you sow.

212
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,120
Good job.

213
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:08,159
I know that one.

214
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:09,440
By the way,

215
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:10,559
are you still going to

216
00:09:10,559 --> 00:09:11,720
Fatty's speech?

217
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:13,279
I forgot.

218
00:09:14,799 --> 00:09:17,759
I'll go change into my...

219
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:19,240
My...

220
00:09:20,559 --> 00:09:21,080
suit.

221
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:21,840
Suit.

222
00:09:22,759 --> 00:09:25,559
I'll go change into my suit.

223
00:09:25,919 --> 00:09:27,240
Don't forget to eat breakfast!

224
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,879
Not coffee and sandwiches again, I hope.

225
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:31,159
This time it's soy milk and fried dough sticks.

226
00:09:31,279 --> 00:09:33,879
Thank you so very much.

227
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:51,720
Thank you, Advisor He.

228
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:53,039
Hold on.

229
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,960
Tomorrow at eight, embassy visa interview.

230
00:09:56,519 --> 00:09:58,639
Here are the interview questions and answers.

231
00:09:58,720 --> 00:09:59,440
Memorize them.

232
00:10:01,759 --> 00:10:03,879
I've always hated memorizing texts.

233
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:05,759
Isn't there another option?

234
00:10:05,919 --> 00:10:07,320
You want a fake marriage with me?

235
00:10:42,279 --> 00:10:43,840
Speech Draft

236
00:10:45,039 --> 00:10:47,840
Archaeology is a discipline

237
00:10:48,039 --> 00:10:50,919
that studies human history.

238
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:52,960
It's not only

239
00:10:53,279 --> 00:10:55,240
the examination of ruins,

240
00:10:56,799 --> 00:11:01,120
but also the organization of historical records,

241
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:03,440
com-

242
00:11:04,879 --> 00:11:07,039
pilation.

243
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,039
Compilation.

244
00:11:10,159 --> 00:11:13,279
The father of Chinese archaeology, Li Ji, once...

245
00:11:13,639 --> 00:11:15,159
Li Ji Zeng, for Chi-

246
00:11:19,679 --> 00:11:21,679
The father of Chinese archaeology is Li Ji.

247
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:24,120
I, I, I know.

248
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:25,320
I know there's no "Zeng."

249
00:11:25,399 --> 00:11:27,240
I was just testing you all, right?

250
00:11:28,399 --> 00:11:29,679
Just a joke.

251
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:33,240
The father of Chinese archaeology, Li Ji,

252
00:11:33,519 --> 00:11:34,480
once

253
00:11:34,639 --> 00:11:37,000
once, for China's archaeological community,

254
00:11:37,399 --> 00:11:38,919
established a rule of the trade.

255
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:43,320
Gulaijin.

256
00:11:43,519 --> 00:11:46,159
Satisfying all your cultural needs.

257
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:47,279
Master Lu,

258
00:11:47,639 --> 00:11:48,879
with teeth like yours,

259
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:50,399
aren't you afraid these sugar-roasted chestnuts

260
00:11:50,399 --> 00:11:51,759
will crack your gold tooth?

261
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:57,519
Stop looking outside.

262
00:11:57,799 --> 00:11:58,840
You won't find me.

263
00:12:01,919 --> 00:12:02,919
Who are you, anyway?

264
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:04,279
Buddy,

265
00:12:04,919 --> 00:12:06,200
if you've got something to say, just say it.

266
00:12:06,639 --> 00:12:08,200
All this sneaking around in the shadows—

267
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:09,080
what's the point?

268
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:10,200
By the way,

269
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:12,919
you missed Fatty's speech today.

270
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:14,559
What a real shame.

271
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:17,120
Who, who, who are you?

272
00:12:17,519 --> 00:12:19,080
Cut the chitchat or I'm hanging up.

273
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:20,600
Listen carefully.

274
00:12:21,159 --> 00:12:22,759
Li Ke has already been taken.

275
00:12:23,519 --> 00:12:24,600
If you don't want him dead,

276
00:12:24,679 --> 00:12:25,919
before five this afternoon,

277
00:12:26,039 --> 00:12:27,840
come to No. 6 Courtyard, Ping'an Hutong.

278
00:12:38,639 --> 00:12:39,559
Then I have a question.

279
00:12:39,559 --> 00:12:40,960
I'd like to ask the two teachers.

280
00:12:41,759 --> 00:12:42,279
Little sister.

281
00:12:42,279 --> 00:12:43,879
Why do you look so familiar?

282
00:12:45,159 --> 00:12:46,279
What "little sister"?

283
00:12:48,039 --> 00:12:50,000
Uh, well, this young lady...

284
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:52,080
I mean, classmate.

285
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:53,840
What's your question?

286
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:57,480
Based on what you said earlier,

287
00:12:57,559 --> 00:12:58,440
the two of you teachers

288
00:12:58,440 --> 00:13:01,080
found this kind of eye totem

289
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:03,240
at two ancient sites in Yunling and Nanyun.

290
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:05,840
Previously, an archaeologist

291
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:07,320
also discovered the same totem

292
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:08,960
in an ancient city in the Western Regions.

293
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:12,320
Does this suggest that these two civilizations

294
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:14,000
share some kind of subtle connection?

295
00:13:14,279 --> 00:13:16,720
Or, if we place this totem

296
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:18,879
within these three civilization systems,

297
00:13:18,879 --> 00:13:20,600
what kind of significance would it have?

298
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:23,960
The eyeball, right?

299
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:25,399
The eye.

300
00:13:25,799 --> 00:13:27,200
The eyeball, the eye, well, it's...

301
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:27,960
It's like this.

302
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:29,080
The eye is our

303
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:30,919
window to exploring the unknown world.

304
00:13:31,279 --> 00:13:33,759
Its shape symbolizes observation.

305
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:35,519
Many civilizations on Earth

306
00:13:35,519 --> 00:13:37,159
also have this kind of eye pattern.

307
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:38,639
As for whether it's

308
00:13:38,639 --> 00:13:40,519
related to those three civilizations,

309
00:13:40,679 --> 00:13:43,519
or whether more unexplored ancient sites

310
00:13:43,519 --> 00:13:45,320
also contain the same totem,

311
00:13:45,639 --> 00:13:47,759
that'll have to be left to our archaeologists

312
00:13:47,759 --> 00:13:48,840
to continue researching.

313
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:50,720
Little Chen.

314
00:13:51,559 --> 00:13:52,279
Little Chen.

315
00:13:53,279 --> 00:13:54,240
Students, please continue.

316
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:55,000
Okay, okay.

317
00:13:55,159 --> 00:13:57,159
Students, let's thank Teacher Chen.

318
00:13:58,159 --> 00:13:59,200
Just now,

319
00:13:59,519 --> 00:14:00,679
I got a phone call.

320
00:14:01,120 --> 00:14:02,039
The person on the other end

321
00:14:02,039 --> 00:14:04,039
not only knew exactly what I was doing,

322
00:14:04,039 --> 00:14:06,440
but also said Fatty had been kidnapped.

323
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:08,799
Fatty's giving a lecture right now.

324
00:14:08,799 --> 00:14:10,120
Could it be a prank?

325
00:14:10,399 --> 00:14:11,559
Prank or not, I don't care.

326
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:12,240
Anyway,

327
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:14,000
I... I won't step out of this courtyard.

328
00:14:20,279 --> 00:14:21,000
Hey, student.

329
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:22,960
The Teacher Fatty who was just lecturing?

330
00:14:23,799 --> 00:14:24,919
I just saw

331
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:26,960
him leave with a man in a suit.

332
00:14:27,039 --> 00:14:27,919
A man in a suit?

333
00:14:27,919 --> 00:14:28,559
Yes.

334
00:14:28,559 --> 00:14:29,320
Thanks.

335
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:31,879
What now?

336
00:14:31,879 --> 00:14:32,919
We've gone around in a huge circle.

337
00:14:32,919 --> 00:14:34,159
Where on earth do we get in?

338
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:35,639
A Guangliang main gate,

339
00:14:35,639 --> 00:14:36,919
a three-courtyard compound,

340
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:39,159
a textbook south-facing house with a southeast gate.

341
00:14:39,919 --> 00:14:41,480
Who lives here?

342
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:43,799
Bro, at a time like this,

343
00:14:43,799 --> 00:14:45,240
why are you pondering that?

344
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:47,559
It's ten minutes to five.

345
00:14:47,799 --> 00:14:48,720
What do we do?

346
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:49,960
Here's the plan, Lao Lu.

347
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:51,200
I'll go in first.

348
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:53,200
If I'm not out in twenty minutes,

349
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:54,840
go to the nearest police station and report it.

350
00:15:01,240 --> 00:15:02,960
Mr. Chen, I've been waiting for you.

351
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:39,919
Please.

352
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:45,240
What took you so long?

353
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:46,000
What's going on?

354
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:46,919
What do you mean, 'what's going on'?

355
00:15:46,919 --> 00:15:48,000
Weren't you about to die?

356
00:15:48,399 --> 00:15:49,679
Drinking yourself to death still counts.

357
00:15:49,679 --> 00:15:50,440
Lao Lu is worried sick about you.

358
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:51,600
Okay, okay, stop, stop.

359
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:52,799
Let me introduce you.

360
00:15:52,799 --> 00:15:53,559
Come on, come on.

361
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:56,279
Uncle Min.

362
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:00,159
A filthy rich Hong Kong businessman.

363
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,039
Let me tell you,

364
00:16:01,440 --> 00:16:02,960
all of our foreign trade dealings,

365
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:05,080
Uncle Min set them all up.

366
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:06,720
All right, all right, Fatty.

367
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:08,639
Brother Chen.

368
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:11,639
I've been waiting forever to meet you.

369
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:12,919
Come, come.

370
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:14,799
Sit down, sit down, let's talk.

371
00:16:14,799 --> 00:16:15,440
Here.

372
00:16:19,360 --> 00:16:21,600
Brother Chen's been in seclusion lately,

373
00:16:21,799 --> 00:16:22,919
not seeing outsiders.

374
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:24,720
So I really had no choice

375
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:26,279
but to resort to this.

376
00:16:26,279 --> 00:16:28,039
I hope you can forgive me, Brother Chen.

377
00:16:29,159 --> 00:16:29,960
Uncle Min.

378
00:16:30,360 --> 00:16:31,279
Lian Ximin.

379
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:33,120
I've got things to do later.

380
00:16:33,679 --> 00:16:35,080
What did you want to see me about?

381
00:16:36,399 --> 00:16:37,559
Straight to the point, as expected.

382
00:16:37,559 --> 00:16:39,000
Yes, yes, that's my buddy.

383
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:39,639
All right.

384
00:16:39,919 --> 00:16:42,240
Then I'll get right to it.

385
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:43,480
No need to beat around the bush.

386
00:16:43,840 --> 00:16:45,240
I invited you here, Brother Chen,

387
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:47,840
because I'd like you to join us

388
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:49,879
on a trip to the western mountains,

389
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:53,240
to search for the legendary Mengna Gu.

